<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Lubricating Oil Pump, Oil
        Filter, and Cooler - Disassemble
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Disassemble</title>
        <svcproc id="s210010902.4" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Disassemble Oil Filter and Header</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently tap on front of oil filter header, with non-metallic hammer, to loosen O-rings.
                    Twist headers and separate from cooler bundle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and inspect oil temperature control thermostat in oil filter and cooler header.
                    Reinstall thermostat with new O-ring.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Depress regulator valve plunger. Insert length of copper wire through regulator valve.
                    Release plunger to trap copper wire in regulator valve.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull copper wire removing regulator valve.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010913" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Oil pressure regulator valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid possible damage to the engine, in case of bearing failure, oil cooler bundle must be
                        replaced. Failed bearing debris cannot be removed from cooler bundle.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disassemble rear and front oil cooler headers from oil cooler bundle.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
